                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="232.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="In today’s digital world, animation relies heavily on powerful software tools and efficient workflows. Whether you're working on 2D or 3D animation, understanding how to navigate animation programs and follow a step-by-step production pipeline is essential. In this chapter, students will explore the most commonly used animation tools and learn how professionals plan, execute, and finalize animated content from concept to completion." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="353.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Animation software provides the digital workspace where artists draw, move, and refine their creations. Programs like Adobe Animate, Toon Boom Harmony, Pencil2D, and Blender are widely used in both education and professional studios. In the Philippines, many animation BPO companies train artists in these platforms because of their global relevance. For example, Blender (which is free and open-source) is increasingly popular among independent Filipino animators for its 3D capabilities, while Adobe Animate remains a strong choice for 2D character animation." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Label layoutX="40.0" layoutY="109.0" prefHeight="53.0" prefWidth="771.0" text="Chapter 3: Animation Tools and Workflows">
                     <font>
